Security Features:
Password Hashing: Uses bcrypt with salt for secure password storage.
JWT Tokens: Secure token-based authentication with expiration.
Input Validation: Basic validation for required fields.
Unique Constraints: Prevents duplicate usernames and emails.
HTTPS Ready: Can be easily deployed with HTTPS in production.

Production Considerations:
Use environment variables for all secrets.
Enable HTTPS in production.
Implement rate limiting.
Add more comprehensive input validation.
Implement token blacklisting for logout functionality.
Set up proper database backups.
Use a process manager like Gunicorn for deployment.
Implement comprehensive logging.
